      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/result/prior-literature-synthesis",
      "type": "uofa:EvidenceNode",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis CFD validation studies",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of twelve published CFD hemolysis validation studies spanning 2008–2022, aggregating power-law exponent estimates, turbulence model performance data, and hemolysis index calibration coefficients from multiple independent research groups. This synthesis consolidates findings from Giersiepen et al. (1990), Bludszuweit (1995), Arora et al. (2004), and subsequent refinements, providing a unified empirical basis for the hemolysis model constants employed in the present COU. The breadth of source material and the cross-laboratory consistency of the aggregated results collectively establish the reliability of the hemolysis model parameterization without need for additional upstream derivation."
    }
